     example it would have been enough to enter only 'test' after
     the prompt, thus setting trace points in all bodies.

     On the other hand it will not always be  necessary  to  have
     trace  or  break  points on all subprograms or packages in a
     declarative part but only on a single subprogram or package.
     To  indicate  this name the particular subprogram or package
     by the selected component notation  and  append  as  a  last
     component '<>'.

     Entering the name 'test.black.<>' would set  only  trace  or
     break points in the body of package 'black'.

     There are four special characters that can be  used  as  the
     first  or  perhaps  only component.  These characters can be
     seen as macro's.  The four characters are:

      1.  !
          the exclaim character will  expand  to  the  unit  name
          given  after  _u_s_e in the status region.  This unit name
          may be changed by the 'use' command.

      2.  #
          the immediate  character  will  expand  to  the  active
          library  unit  name.   The  active  library unit is the
          first (or  perhaps  only)  component  in  the  selected
          component  name  displayed  after  the  word  _i_n on the
          status region.

      3.  $
          the dollar character expands to the selected  component
          name  given after the word _i_n on the status region.  In
          effect this is the active subprogram or package.

      4.  *
          the star character may only be used as  the  first  and
          only  component  in the name.  The effect of its use is
          to set trace or break points  in  all  subprograms  and
          packages of the DAS program.

